This woman has a graceful look to her. The slightly pointed ears combined with the lines worn into her face point to the woman's likely partial elven lineage.

Her brown hair is cut to mid length and parted on her right side, and her eyes are sharp green. Her fine, silken attire, paired with gold and jewels, points to an affluent life. She wields an ironwood staff that glows with magical energy.

She bears no particular markings or religious symbols, but clearly favors white and blue tones.

Arcane Defiance Armors all contain this same inscription:

"Throughout the realms the wielders of magic are advantaged over the common people. We stand in defiance of their tyranny and casual attitudes to power"

Who we are is unknown, but the protection from magic that these items provide is superior.

Forged from the ancient wood of a birch tree, this staff stands as a conduit to the profound wisdom of the natural world. Its gnarled yet elegant form, adorned with delicate engravings resembling ancient runes, exudes a calming aura. When grasped, the staff imparts a serene enlightenment, enriching the wielder's connection with the world around them. The staff becomes a vessel for the whispers of ancient spirits, instilling in its possessor a deep well of wisdom and sagacity. As the staff channels the tranquil energies of the earth, it not only enhances the wielder's discernment but also envelops them in an aura of tranquil contemplation, a source of timeless insight amidst the chaotic currents of existence which gives its priestly caster the ability to cast more spells.
